  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A blend of dragon-scaled herbs and powdered tongue-coal, prepared by Shen Feng Wa's surviving apprentices. Burns clean only in the bowl of the Dubious Pipe; in any other vessel it produces foul black smoke and nothing else.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 hour you have a +2 bonus to Wisdom (Insight) checks and your passive Perception increases by 2.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Wa's Reserve (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Wa's Reserve.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Charisma checks (the smoke leaves a black residue on the tongue).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 3.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(3 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Shen Feng Wa's Dubious Pipe.</em></p>"
    },
